Iteration 2 capture receipt of channel_ready as a state. This highlights the state explosion that happens with an additional piece of data. Additionally this now captures the connected event WITHOUT transitioning state since we only transition upon receipt of channel_reestablish, this assumes that we have already sent channel_reestablish to the peer by the time we received the peer's channel_reestablish message.
We still keep connected and disconnected as split graphs to highlight that there are different actions necessary.
Note: numbering of transitions has not been corrected as of 2/21/23.
